WEBVTT

00:08:29.848 --> 00:08:32.852
a very useful way of thinking.

00:08:32.852 --> 00:08:35.130
It's not just families either.

00:08:35.130 --> 00:08:37.255
The medical professionals too,

00:08:37.255 --> 00:08:40.615
you out there, you're in denial too.

00:08:40.615 --> 00:08:43.468
You want to help. You want to fix.

00:08:43.468 --> 00:08:45.294
You want to do.

00:08:45.294 --> 00:08:48.102
You've succeeded in everything you've done,

00:08:48.102 --> 00:08:50.144
and having a patient die,

00:08:50.144 --> 00:08:53.723
well, that must feel like failure.

00:08:53.723 --> 00:08:55.567
I saw it firsthand.

00:08:55.567 --> 00:08:58.269
Just days before Terence died,

00:08:58.269 --> 00:09:00.287
his oncologist said,